Do you really think that anyone really benefitted from the Cold War? I don't think that this was a vehicle that allowed opportunities for anyone to benefit. There was much chaos (riotings, attempted political coups, confusion, disgruntleness (women, blacks, minorities) due to the racisms, inequalities, tensions from nuclear armament, and on both sides (US and the Soviets), as well as great tension throughout the world for fear of nuclear holocaust! Where is the benefit? Just a thought.  
