===message:I would have to say that I agree with Conswella on this issue. I believe the U.S. and the Soviets both benefited from the Cold War. I understand Leon's point about the large amount of suffering among the people of the two countries. The people that suffered the most was the common people, not the government as a whole. I believe the citizens of these countries had differing opinions than that of their respective governments. The ordinary people just wanted peace, food, and the opportunity to give their families a better life. They weren't worried about who the superpowers were or what these "superpowers" were trying to accomplish. They wanted what everyone else wanted, Peace! Now that's my thought. Thanks. :)
